        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: harden diff and approval state writes",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Treat corrupt diff snapshots as cache misses and rewrite them atomically.\n- Treat corrupt approval ID index entries as expired/missing instead of crashing resume.\n- Preserve no-overwrite approval index writes with a hard-link atomic path, plus a direct `wx` exclusive-create fallback for filesystems that do not support hard links.\n- Removed the PR-owned changelog entry so release notes stay release-owned.\n\n## Review follow-up\n- Added the requested portability path for hard-link failures (`ENOSYS`, `ENOTSUP`, `EOPNOTSUPP`, `EPERM`, `EXDEV`) without overwriting an existing approval mapping.\n- Added test coverage for the unsupported-hard-link fallback and the existing no-overwrite guarantee.\n\n## Proof\nRuntime proof from the built code:\n\n```text\ndiff-corrupt-proof {\"before\":null,\"changed\":true,\"after\":{\"ok\":true}}\napproval-resume-exit=2\napproval-resume-stdout={\n  \"protocolVersion\": 1,\n  \"ok\": false,\n  \"error\": {\n    \"type\": \"parse_error\",\n    \"message\": \"Approval ID \\\"deadbeef\\\" not found or expired\"\n  }\n}\napproval-resume-stderr=\nexclusive-fallback-proof {\"mode\":\"600\",\"secondCode\":\"EEXIST\",\"content\":\"{\\\"stateKey\\\":\\\"original\\\"}\\n\"}\n```\n\n## Validation\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run format`\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run build`\n- `node --test dist/test/state.test.js dist/test/approval_id.test.js --test-name-pattern 'corrupt|approval index writes never overwrite|writeFileAtomicExclusive|falls back'`\n- `pnpm --config.minimum-release-age=0 run test` (247 tests passed)\n",
